casebody.data:
Howard SOHN, Appellant(s)/Petitioner(s),
v.
U.S. BANK, N.A., Appellee(s)/Respondent(s), CASE NO.: 3D17-2035 District Court of Appeal of Florida, Third District. NOVEMBER 17, 2017 SUAREZ, LAGOA and SCALES, JJ., concur.

Upon consideration, appellant's motion to relinquish jurisdiction is hereby denied.

ORDERED that appellee's motion to dismiss appeal for lack of jurisdiction is granted, and this appeal from the Circuit Court for Miami-Dade County, Florida is hereby dismissed without prejudice to timely filing a notice of appeal after an appealable final order has been entered by the trial court.
